detailed_steps: BSS (balanced salt solution) and anesthetic insertion
Main port wound creation - 2 or 3 plane wound insertion created temporally  2 plane insertion: Angle blade upwards slightly first then insert blade horizontally into anterior chamber
Creation of anterior capsulotomy with utrata forceps
Insert cannula tip under anterior capsule and insert BSS to separate lens from capsule   Signs of hydrodissection Wave  Nucleus lift  Nucleus prolapse   Rotate the nucleus
Irrigation and aspiration of soft lens material with I/A Probe
Insert OVD to fill the capsular bag
Use injector to insert lens into capsular bag
Rotate the lens into the capsular bag
Use I/A probe to aspirate viscoat from bag and angles of the eye
Hydrate the side ports and main port wounds using BSS cannula
Insertion of triamcinolone (steroid medication) and moxifloxacin (antibiotics) - unique to this case
Hydrate the side ports and main port wounds using BSS cannula
Check eye pressure  Use side of BSS cannula to lightly depress onto eye to assess the intra ocular pressure If too firm, release some fluid from the side or main port wound
Check the wounds to ensure they are water tight  No leakage of fluid when wounds swiped with cotton gauze swab
Limbal relaxing incision to reduce astigmatism
